# Build + run byproducts. The fixture is lifted by PARSING its source, not by
# compiling it; `target/` only appears because the rust-analyzer oracle runs
# `cargo metadata`. The `.provekit/runs/` proofs and `.provekit/imports/` dep
# proof are regenerated by `provekit mint` (the imports shim proof is minted
# from examples/provekit-shim-rust-std and copied in by scripts/self-apply.sh
# or the runbook flow), so they are not checked in.
/target/
/Cargo.lock
.provekit/runs/
.provekit/imports/
